Author-Name: Jason Abaluck  
Author-Name: Jonathan Gruber  
Title: Choice Inconsistencies among the Elderly: Evidence from Plan Choice in the Medicare Part D Program 
Abstract:
 We evaluate the choices of elders across their insurance options under the
 Medicare Part D Prescription Drug plan, using a unique dataset of
 prescription drug claims matched to information on the characteristics of
 choice sets. We document that elders place much more weight on plan
 premiums than on expected out-of-pocket costs; value plan financial
 characteristics beyond any impacts on their own financial expenses or
 risk; and place almost no value on variance- reducing aspects of plans.
 Partial equilibrium welfare analysis implies that welfare would have been
 27 percent higher if patients had all chosen rationally. (JEL D12, I11,
 J14)
