Author-Name: Gary Charness  
Author-Name: Martin Dufwenberg  
Title: Participation 
Abstract:
 We show experimentally that whether and how communication achieves
 beneficial social outcomes in a hidden-information context depends
 crucially on whether low-talent agents can participate in a
 Pareto-improving outcome. Communication is effective (and patterns of lies
 and truth quite systematic) when this is feasible, but otherwise
 completely ineffective. We examine the data in light of two potentially
 relevant behavioral models: cost-of-lying and guilt-fromblame. (JEL D82,
 D83, Z13) 
