Template-Type: ReDIF-Article 1.0
Author-Name: Benjamin Lester  
Title: Information and Prices with Capacity Constraints 
Abstract:
 In the theoretical literature on consumer search, one conclusion is nearly
 universal: as buyers become better able to observe and compare prices ex
 ante, sellers will set lower prices in equilibrium. In this paper, I
 examine a standard consumer search model with one small -- yet often
 relevant -- additional restriction: I assume that sellers are capacity
 constrained. In this environment, I illustrate that the conventional
 wisdom regarding information and prices does not necessarily hold: having
 more informed consumers can lead to a decrease in prices, have no effect
 at all, or even lead to an increase in prices.
